# Blackjack AI Assistant MVP

## Project Summary

The Blackjack AI Assistant is an AI-powered decision-support and training tool for casual and intermediate blackjack players. A user enters their current blackjack hand and the dealer’s visible card, and the system returns a recommended action such as Hit, Stand, Double, or Split. The system combines a rules-based blackjack engine for reliable strategy recommendations with an optional nanoGPT-style language model that explains the recommendation in plain English.

Our original project idea included both blackjack and poker decision support. For the course MVP, we intentionally narrowed the scope to blackjack so we could deliver a working, reproducible system with a user interface, a recommendation engine, and an explanation model within the course timeline. Poker is left as future work. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0} :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

## What the MVP Does

This MVP allows a user to:

- enter player cards
- enter the dealer upcard
- choose whether doubling and splitting are allowed
- optionally provide additional player cards if the hand already has more than two cards
- receive a recommended action from the blackjack strategy engine
- see a plain-English explanation of the recommendation
- optionally generate an explanation using a trained nanoGPT-style model if checkpoints are available

The system is intended as a blackjack training and strategy-learning tool rather than a full casino-grade simulation system. The current engine uses rules-based basic-strategy-style logic and a heuristic confidence score. It is not a full expected-value simulator. :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2} :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}

